parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, and potentially life-threatening situations, such as stalling on a busy highway.
symptoms: The temperature gauge rises to "H"
steam is visible under the hood
the engine overheats
coolant leaks
oil mixes with antifreeze
and the vehicle may suddenly stall or accelerate uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncontrolled acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates to full throttle
the accelerator pedal does not respond
and the vehicle may maintain a high speed even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pan gasket can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially costly repairs.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil pan
oil plugs break
and the engine may experience premature wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ingress of exhaust fumes into the vehicle can cause health problems, dizziness, and disorientation, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Exhaust fumes are present inside the vehicle while driving with the windows up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadvertent or improper airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, or accidents, and may lead to windshield damage, roof caving, or seatbelt failures.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
airbag covers disengage
airbags shatter windshields
airbags cause injuries
seatbelts fail to restrain passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Booster Vacuum Hose Check Valve Freeze
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the check valve in the brake booster vacuum hose can cause a loss of power assist braking, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels normal on the first application
but subsequent applications result in no power assist
requiring multiple pumps of the brake pedal to restore normal braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The anti-skid system can malfunction in packed snow and ice conditions, releasing rapidly and continuously, destroying deceleration capability, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: When applying the brakes gently on a downhill slope
the anti-skid system releases rapidly
causing the vehicle to accelerate instead of decelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ABS system can overcompensate in icy or slick conditions, resulting in no significant braking, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle sails through intersections during icy conditions
and the system does not perform as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Warped Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause the brakes to pulse, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes pulse when applied
indicating warped rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can suddenly accelerate when applying the brakes, causing extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to accelerate when applying the brakes
resulting in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the hill holder system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and even catastrophic losses.
symptoms: Unrecoverable yawed slide/skid
loss of vehicle control
inability to stop the vehicle
sudden acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission binding in turns can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and even damage to the vehicle's axles.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates or binds when turning
difficulty steering
unusual noises or vibrations when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Improper Tire Size and Rear Differential Overheating
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of improper tire size and overheating of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire
unusual noises or smells from the rear differential
excessive heat emanating from the rear of the vehicle.
